No ke komo ʻana i kou waihona haumāna (ma ka inoa/helu haumāna) :

  • E holoi i ka māka o loko o ka pahu no ka "Haumāna Kipa"
  • E hoʻokomo ʻoe i kou Inoa Mua a me kou Helu Haumāna i loko o nā puka o luna.

No ke kāinoa ʻana ma ke ʻano he haumāna (Haumāna Kipa) :

  • E māka i ka pahu no ka "Haumāna Kipa" (E ʻike ʻia ʻo Haumāna Kipa ma nā wahi ʻelua)
  • E kaomi i ke [Kāinoa] no ke omo ʻana i ka Hōʻike Hoʻomaʻamaʻa ma ke ʻano he haumāna kipa.

Wā Hana Haumāna Kipa?
Ma loko o ka Wā Hana Haumāna Kipa, ʻaʻole pono ka ʻāpono ʻana mai o ka luna hōʻike a hiki iā ʻoe ke hana i kekahi Hōʻike Hoʻomaʻamaʻa me ka hoʻohana ʻana i kou mau hiʻohiʻona. No ka hana ʻana i ka Hōʻike Hoʻomaʻamaʻa ma kekahi wā hana me ka luna hōʻike, e holoi i ka māka o ka pahu no ka "Wā Hana Haumāna Kipa" a e hoʻokomo i ka Helu Wā Hana i nā puka ma mua o ke kaomi ʻana i ka [Kāinoa].

Para iniciar sesión con una cuenta de estudiante (con Nombre / SSID):

  • desactive la selección de la casilla de verificación “Usuario invitado” (ambos campos aparecerán vacíos)
  • Ingrese su nombre y SSID en esos campos.

Para iniciar sesión como invitado (usuario anónimo):

  • Marque la casilla de verificación "Usuario invitado" (ambos campos mostrarán automáticamente Invitado)
  • Haga clic en [Iniciar sesión] para iniciar sesión en la prueba de muestra como usuario invitado.

¿Sesión de invitado?
En una sesión de invitado, no necesita la aprobación del administrador de la prueba, por lo que puede realizar la prueba con su propia configuración. Para realizar la prueba de muestra en una sesión con el administrador de la prueba, desactive la selección de la casilla de verificación “Sesión de invitado” e ingrese el id. de sesión en el campo antes de hacer clic en [Iniciar sesión].

Client_MessageTranslation.Message:
Starting the Test Session:

  • Select the test(s) that need to be included in the session, then click the [Start Session] button.
  • Provide the Session ID to your students so that they can log in.

Approving Students:

  • Click the [Approvals (#)] button. The Approvals and Student Test Settings window will appear.
  • Click [See/Edit Details] for a student to view his or her accommodations and test settings and make any necessary changes (e.g., color background choice).
  • Click the [Approve] button for each student to allow entry into the session.
  • Click [Approve All Students] if all their settings are accurate and they can all enter the session.
  • To deny a student, click [Deny] and enter a brief reason (e.g., student selected the wrong test).

Note: Once students are approved, their settings for the current opportunity cannot be changed.


Student Lookup:

You can use this feature to look up student information if a student is having difficulty logging in.

  • Click the [Student Lookup] button in the top row.
  • Use the [Quick Search] tab to find a student using his or her MARSS/SSID number. Partial entries are not allowed.
  • Use the [Advanced Search] tab to find a student by district, school, and first or last name. Partial names are allowed. (e.g., entering "Fi" into the last name field will start a search for all students in the school whose last name begins with Fi).

Monitoring Student Progress:

Students who appear in the table below have entered this session. The page automatically refreshes every minute. When the page refreshes, the students’ statuses in the table below will update. The current status plus (#/#) will indicate how many questions have been answered by the student.


Stopping the Test Session:

  • When all students have completed testing or it is time for the session to end, click [Stop Session].
  • This will end the session, pause all your students' tests and then log them out of the online testing system.

  • Haga clic en [Iniciar sesión] para iniciar sesión en la prueba de muestra como usuario invitado.

¿Sesión de invitado?
En una sesión de invitado, no necesita la aprobación del administrador de la prueba, por lo que puede realizar la prueba con su propia configuración. Para realizar la prueba de muestra en una sesión con el administrador de la prueba, desactive la selección de la casilla de verificación “Sesión de invitado” e ingrese el id. de sesión en el campo antes de hacer clic en [Iniciar sesión].

Client_MessageTranslation.Message:
Welcome to the Minnesota Assessments Online Item Samplers!

Anyone can access these online item samplers using the guest login options. Students may also use their first name and 13-digit MARSS/SSID number to log into a practice session or a guest session.

To log in with your student account (using your name and MARSS/SSID number):

  • Un-check the "Guest User" check box (both fields will become blank)
  • Enter your first name and MARSS/SSID number in the fields above.

To log in as a Guest (anonymous user) in a Guest Session:

  • Make sure the "Guest User" check box is checked (both fields will automatically display Guest)
  • Click [Sign In] to log into the Online Item Samplers as a guest user.

About Guest Sessions:

Guest sessions do not require Test Monitor approval. You can see the item samplers using your own settings.

To enter a practice session with a Test Monitor:

  • Un-check the “Guest Session” check box.
  • Enter the Session ID, and then click [Sign In].

En una sesión de invitado, no necesita la aprobación del administrador de la prueba, por lo que puede realizar la prueba con su propia configuración. Para realizar la prueba de muestra en una sesión con el administrador de la prueba, desactive la selección de la casilla de verificación “Sesión de invitado” e ingrese el id. de sesión en el campo antes de hacer clic en [Iniciar sesión].

  • Ingrese su nombre y SSID en esos campos.

  • Haga clic en [Iniciar sesión] para iniciar sesión en la prueba de muestra como usuario invitado.

¿Sesión de invitado?
En una sesión de invitado, no necesita la aprobación del administrador de la prueba, por lo que puede realizar la prueba con su propia configuración. Para realizar la prueba de muestra en una sesión con el administrador de la prueba, desactive la selección de la casilla de verificación “Sesión de invitado” e ingrese el id. de sesión en el campo antes de hacer clic en [Iniciar sesión].

Client_MessageTranslation.Message:
Starting the Session:

  • Select the Item Sampler(s) that need to be included in the session, then click the [Start Session] button.
  • Provide the Session ID to your students so that they can log in.

Approving Students:

  • Click the [Approvals (#)] button. The Approvals and Student Test Settings window will appear.
  • Click [See/Edit Details] for a student to view his or her accommodations and test settings and make any necessary changes (e.g., color background choice).
  • Click the [Approve] button for each student to allow entry into the session.
  • Click [Approve All Students] if all of their settings are accurate and they can all enter the session.
  • To deny a student, click [Deny] and enter a brief reason (e.g., student selected the wrong item sampler).

Note: Once students are approved, their settings for the current opportunity cannot be changed.


Student Lookup:

You can use this feature to look up student information if a student is having difficulty logging in.

  • Click the [Student Lookup] button in the top row.
  • Use the [Quick Search] tab to find a student using his or her MARSS/SSID number. Partial entries are not allowed.
  • Use the [Advanced Search] tab to find a student by district, school, and first or last name. Partial names are allowed. (e.g., entering "Fi" into the last name field will start a search for all students in the school whose last name begins with Fi).

Monitoring Student Progress:

Students who appear in the table below have entered this session. The page automatically refreshes every minute. When the page refreshes, the students’ statuses in the table below will update. The current status plus (#/#) will indicate how many questions have been answered by the student.


Stopping the Test Session:

  • When all students have completed testing or it is time for the session to end, click [Stop Session].
  • This will end the session, pause all your students' tests and then log them out of the online testing system.

Click on the [Tests] button to view or add tests to your session.

Starting the Session:

  • Select the assessment(s) that need to be included in the session, then click the [Start Session] button.
  • Provide the Session ID to your students so that they can log in.

Approving Students:

  • Click the [Approvals (#)] button. The Approvals and Student Test Settings window will appear.
  • Click [See/Edit Details] for a student to view his or her accommodations and test settings and make any necessary changes (e.g., color background choice).
  • Click the [Approve] button for each student to allow entry into the session.
  • Click [Approve All Students] if all their settings are accurate and they can all enter the session.
  • To deny a student, click [Deny] and enter a brief reason (e.g., student selected the wrong assessment).

Note: Once students are approved, their settings for the current opportunity cannot be changed.

Student Lookup:

You can use this feature to look up student information if a student is having difficulty logging in.

  • Click the [Student Lookup] button in the top row.
  • Use the [Quick Lookup] tab to find a student using his or her SSID number. Partial SSIDs are not allowed.
  • Use the [Advanced Search] tab to find a student by complex area, school, and first or last name. Partial names are allowed. (e.g., entering "Fi" into the last name field will start a search for all students in the school whose last name begins with Fi).

Monitoring Student Progress:

Students that appear in the table below have entered this session. The page automatically refreshes every minute. When the page refreshes, the students’ statuses in the table below will update. The current status plus (#/#) will indicate how many test items have been presented to the student out of the total number of test items in the assessment. This does not mean that the student has answered all the questions so far. (For example, a student can be viewing a page that has 5 items, but not yet answered all the items on that page.)

Stopping the Test Session

  • When all students have completed testing or it is time for the session to end, click [Stop Session].
  • This will end the session, pause all your students' assessments and then log them out of the online testing system.

TDS_CoreMessageObject.AppKey: Select a field test report to generate
TDS_CoreMessageObject.Message: Step 1: Select a field test report to generate

Legend

Latency—How long it takes the system to generate a request

Client-selection—The amount of time in milliseconds the browser waits when it requests the next item group from the adaptive selection algorithm (including all SSL encryptions/decryptions)

Client-review—The amount of time the browser waits when it requests a previously-selected item group for review (including SSL)

Server-selection—The amount of time the server requires to complete an item-selection request (does not include SSL encryption/decryption)

Server-review—The amount of time the server requires to complete an item-group review request (not including SSL)

Min/max/mean ms—The minimum, maximum and mean time (in milliseconds) taken to generate the request

dbmin/dbmax/dbmean—The amount of the server overall time consumed by the dominant database query
This report shows data for both server and browser (client-side) latency times in milliseconds.
